article.headline: UTEP 62, Houston 55
article.story: HOUSTON -- Arnett Moultrie had a double-double with 19 points and 18 rebounds to lead UTEP to a 62-55 win over Houston on Wednesday night. Randy Culpepper scored 13, Stefon Jackson added 12 and Julyan Stone contributed 11 steals for UTEP (12-8, 3-3 CUSA). Marcus Cousin scored a double-double for Houston (12-6, 3-2 CUSA) with 15 points and 13 rebounds. DaShaun Williams scored 13, Kelvin Lewis added 11 and Desmond Wade contributed 10 for UTEP. UTEP led 37-21 at the half. The Miners held a 51-34 rebounding edge.
